; square.anal — first-class subroutines via PASSAGE.
;
; PASSAGEs share the global stack — there are no locals. The body runs
; on whatever is on top when ENTER is called, and leaves its result(s)
; on the stack for the caller. PASSAGE declarations must appear before
; the main body.

ANAL "square" VERSION 1

PASSAGE square:
  DUP
  MUL
EXIT

PUSH 9
ENTER square
DISCHARGE
; Output: 81

PUSH 4
ENTER square
ENTER square
DISCHARGE
; Output: 256   (4 squared = 16; 16 squared = 256)
